                <head>78. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>House and Senate conferees reported a compromise version of S. 3420 to extend
                    P.L. 480 on August 22. Both the House and the Senate passed the bill that day.
                    S. 3420 thus became P.L. 85–931, which President <persName corresp="#p_EDD1"
                        >Eisenhower</persName> signed on September 6. As enacted, P.L. 85–931
                    extended P.L. 480 for 18 months until December 31, 1959, and increased the
                    authorization for foreign currency sales from $4 billion to $6.25 billion. For
                    text of P.L. 85–931, see <hi rend="italic">American Foreign Policy: Current
                        Documents, 1958,</hi> pages 1535–1538.</p>
            </div>
